From de981da98cf929b4e91c1387f6858b3aae03789c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: vllm-shim <vllm-shim@local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(triton): ship gfx942 default config for
 GEMM-AFP4WFP4

aiter/ops/triton/utils/gemm_config_utils.py::get_gemm_config requires
the default {arch}-{config_name}.json to exist (fpath_should_exist=True)
and raises AssertionError otherwise. The upstream configs/gemm tree
ships GEMM-AFP4WFP4 only for gfx1250, so any caller of gemm_afp4wfp4
on gfx942 crashes at model init -- e.g. Quark MXFP4 checkpoints
(amd/Kimi-K2.6-MXFP4) whose shared experts route through
quark_w4a4_mxfp4.apply_weights -> gemm_afp4wfp4.

Adds a hand-rolled gfx942 default. Values aren't auto-tuned: they are
chosen conservatively to fit MI300X's 64KB LDS budget (BLOCK_SIZE_K=128,
num_stages=2), keep matrix_instr_nonkdim=16 so tl.dot_scaled decomposes
to BF16 m16n16k16 MFMA, and cover the standard M_LEQ bucket ladder plus
an 'any' fallback. Performance is sub-optimal until someone tunes for
gfx942, but the model launches and produces correct output.

The gfx1250 default ships BLOCK_SIZE_K=256 with num_stages=3, which
needs ~96KB LDS for the B tile alone and won't compile on gfx942, so it
can't be reused as-is.

Not upstreamed.
